          <item row="0" column="0">
           <widget class="QLabel" name="label_3">
            <property name="text">
             <string>&lt;html&gt;&lt;head/&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;p&gt;If the patient images were processed with &lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;FreeSurfer&lt;/span&gt;, simply select the FreeSurfer output folder. All required data will be loaded and labelled automatically.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you have a DICOM, you can also include it in the root folder inside of another folder.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If FreeSurfer was not used, you can still use this feature by selecting a folder containing the following files:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 2;&quot;&gt;&lt;li style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Brain label map: aseg.mgz&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Masked brain: norm.mgz&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;T1-weighted MRI: T1.mgz&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Cortical surfaces: rh.pial, rh.white, lh.pial, lh.white&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;A folder with the CT scan DICOM files &lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;If some of these files are missing, the import will still run, but only the available data will be loaded. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Select the file/folder:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
            </property>
            <property name="textFormat">
